Boston Mayor Thomas Menino has passed away, and Vice President Joe Biden has released a statement expressing his condolences. Biden describes Menino as a long-time friend and one of the finest mayors the nation has ever seen. He praises Menino's dedication to his city, calling him the very definition of "Boston Strong." Biden also highlights Menino's heroic actions following the Boston Marathon bombing, where he remained calm and resolute. Menino's commitment to protecting his city extended to addressing issues such as gun violence as a leading member of Mayors Against Illegal Guns. The Vice President also mentions his collaboration with Menino on improving Boston's neighborhoods, schools, housing, and infrastructure. Biden concludes by stating that Menino's legacy will live on in the city he loved and in the example he set for public servants everywhere. He describes Menino as a good man who earned the highest compliment the Irish can give.